  <front>
   <head>SONG VI. The Attribute of VENUS.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">YES; Fulvia is like Venus fair;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Has all her bloom, and shape and air:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But still, to perfect every grace,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">She wants â€” the smile upon her face.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The crown majestic Juno wore;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And Cynthia's brow the crescent bore,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">An helmet mark'd Minerva's mien,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But smiles distinguish'd Beauty's queen.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her train was form'd of smiles of loves</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her chariot drawn by gentlest doves;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And from her zone, the nymph may find,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis Beauty's province to be kind.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then smile, my fair; and all whose aim</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Aspires to paint the Cyprian dame,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or bid her breathe in living stone,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Shall take their forms from you alone.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
